        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): crabline channel driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR makes QA profile channel drivers executable rather than descriptive metadata.\n\n- Routes the `smoke-ci` QA profile through the Crabline SDK-backed channel driver, with Telegram as the first supported Crabline channel.\n- Adds a Crabline-backed QA transport that drives inbound Telegram scenarios through Crabline and observes OpenClaw replies through the existing QA Lab bus.\n- Uses the existing QA credential broker path so the lane can run locally from env vars or in CI from Convex credential leases.\n- Adds profile scenario filtering for targeted taxonomy-backed smoke runs.\n- Adds a CI lane that runs the `smoke-ci` profile with Crabline and Convex credential leases.\n- Makes the `release` live profile fan out to the native Matrix, Telegram, Discord, Slack, and WhatsApp live lane catalogs, then merges their native `qa-evidence.json` files into one profile evidence artifact.\n- Converts Matrix live QA to emit native QA evidence while preserving its Matrix-specific diagnostic summary.\n- Keeps Crabline as a QA Lab dev-only dependency and lazy-loads it outside the production OpenClaw bundle.\n\n## Why\n\n`smoke-ci` is intended to prove the taxonomy-selected CI profile against an SDK-backed channel path with deterministic model providers. `release` is intended to collect real live-channel evidence from the existing bespoke live lane catalogs. This PR wires those profile choices into actual execution and shared QA evidence so profile scorecards represent real channel coverage instead of metadata-only declarations.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions --pretty false`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test --pretty false`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/evidence-summary.test.ts extensions/qa-matrix/src/runners/contract/runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-matrix/src/cli.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/telegram/telegram-live.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/discord/discord-live.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/slack/slack-live.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/whatsapp-live.runtime.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
